People fleeing from the collapsing tent. Picture: TwitterJOHANNESBURG. &#8211; President Jacob Zuma had to stop mid-speech when the tent he was in collapsed at a Day of Reconciliation event in Gopane, North West, on Friday. A fierce storm saw all news broadcasts cut and people stampeding out after the marquee&#8217;s top was lifted in the air by strong winds. Before the tent&#8217;s collapse, President Zuma was enjoying a warm reception from the crowd as he conducted a lengthy history lesson on various aspects of the holiday.As he turned to the topic of Marikana, declaring, &#8220;The incident was painful and traumatic not only for the families but all South Africans&#8221;, the tent collapsed. President Zuma was subsequently removed from the venue by his bodyguards. News24 